definitions.definition: A right tributary of the Seine , in eastern France , flowing 319 miles east and southeast of Paris through the departments of Haute-Marne , Marne , Aisne , Seine-et-Marne , Seine-Saint-Denis and Val-de-Marne .
A department of Grand Est , France . Capital: Châlons-en-Champagne ( INSEE code 51).
